{"summary":"Accept the two real state-management defects: stale idle status after partial-failure repair and the unlocked read-then-append race in start idempotence. Reject the timestamp-fallback note because it mostly documents an inherent legacy-data ambiguity, and reject the duplicate-collapse note as a low-value optimization rather than a robustness issue.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-5-54b32534","decision":"reject","rationale":"The mixed `run_id`/`started_at` fallback is the intentional legacy-compatibility heuristic, and the suggested tightening is already how the match works in practice. The remaining ambiguity only exists because legacy rows lack a durable identifier; without more persisted data this cannot be made materially safer, so this reads as documentation polish rather than a substantive correctness amendment."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-3ee9bde4","decision":"reject","rationale":"This is redundant work, but not a correctness, safety, or robustness defect. Keeping `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` responsible for its own normalization preserves a cleaner invariant for callers; changing signatures just to avoid one extra collapse in `record_bead_start` is a minor optimization with limited maintainability payoff."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-15b1f41e","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real repair bug. If `record_bead_start` appends lineage but fails before writing `status.json`, a later completion replay can leave the snapshot in `planning` or another stale non-terminal status even though lineage shows the run finished. Reconciliation should derive the correct idle execution status from lineage whenever there is no active bead, not only when the prior snapshot happened to be `active`."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-ef6f1e4a","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real concurrency defect. `record_bead_start` does unlocked read-then-append checks for both lineage and journal emission, so concurrent retries of the same `(bead_id, project_id, run_id)` can both insert running rows and both emit `BeadStarted`. Later collapse can repair lineage, but not duplicate journal history or transient snapshot overcounts; the start idempotence check needs a single serialized compare-and-insert path."}]}